  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is considered a criminal offense in most countries and falls under criminal legislation. Specifically:\n\n1. It is typically classified as a serious financial crime\n\n2. Laws against money laundering are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income\n\n3. Penalties can include:\n- Heavy fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal record\n\n4. Many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations\n\n5. Financial institutions are required to report suspicious transactions that might indicate money laundering\n\nThe exact legal specifics can vary between jurisdictions, but it is universally treated as a criminal activity.",
